Members of the Authority shall be persons who have adequate knowledge and experience in any one or more of the following functional areas-
* energy supply and demand, including the end use consumption of energy;
<\li1>

Members of the Authority shall be persons who have adequate knowledge and experience in any one or more of the following functional areas-
* energy supply and demand, including the end use consumption of energy;
<\li1>
* commercial and business practices and procedures;
* financial and funding aspects of the energy sector;
* energy tariffs, pricing or charges;
* energy planning and project development;
* energy technology and standards or renewable energy technologies;
* environmental issues; or
* legal matters.
* is a Member of Parliament;
* is a Minister or Deputy Minister;
* is a holder of a licence;
* is an employee of a licensee;
* is a director of a company holding a licence under this Act;
* holds five per cent or more shares in a company holding a licence under this Act;
* has been convicted of an offence under this Act, or an offence involving fraud or dishonesty by a competent court in Malawi or elsewhere;
* is in a position where there is a material conflict of interest between the interests of the member as member of the Authority and the business interest of that member, shall be disqualified from being appointed as a member of the Authority.

(1) The Authority shall have power to regulate the activities of the energy industry in accordance with this Act and the Energy Laws and without limitation to the generality of the foregoing, shall carry out the following functions
* receive and process licence applications for energy undertaking;
* grant, revoke or amend licences granted under this Act and Energy Laws;
* approve tariffs, and prices of energy sales and services;
* monitor and enforce compliance by licensees with licences granted under this Act and the Energy Laws;
* develop and enforce performance and safety standards for energy exploitation, production transportation and distribution;
* prescribe and collect fees, charges, levies or rates under this Act and Energy Laws;
* arbitrate commercial disputes under this Act and Energy Laws;
* Recommend reforms to this Act and the Energy Laws as the Authority may deem desirable;
* Resolve or mediate consumer complaints against licensees; and
* do all such things as are necessary or incidental or conducive to the better carrying out of the functions of the Authority provided for in this Act and Energy Laws.
* promote the interests of consumers of energy with respect to energy prices and charges and the continuity and quality of energy supply;
* monitor the efficiency and performance of energy undertakings, having regard to the purposes for which they were established;

The annual report referred to in subsection (1) shall include:
* an audited balance sheet and income statement, including any notes thereon and documents annexed thereto whereby relevant information is provided;
* the report of the examination of the accounts referred to in section 26 (3);
* information regarding licences granted, renewed, amended, suspended, cancelled or withdrawn;
* information regarding the amount of rural electrification levies collected and paid to the Rural Electrification Fund;
* a report regarding the execution of the business plan of the Authority;
* a report of the future strategic plans of the Authority;
* a status report on the performance of the energy sector and energy undertakings; and
* such other information as the Authority may from time to time deem necessary.
* to determine whether any person is carrying on or involved in any energy undertaking; and
* to order any person not holding a licence and who is obliged to apply for and hold a licence under this Act or Energy Laws to cease carrying on or being involved in any energy undertaking.
